{"type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","name":"EngramMemSave","input":{"project":"mastra-101-new","type":"bugfix","content":"**What**: Fixed an unhandled frontend crash in OpenChamber UI. Created empty `{}` `openchamber.json` files globally and in the active project.\n**Why**: OpenChamber's frontend `main.js` threw an unhandled promise rejection when fetching `openchamber.json` if it did not exist (API returned 404). This crashed the UI entirely, showing \"Chat Error\". By providing `{}` in both `~/.config/openchamber/openchamber.json` and the project's `.openchamber/openchamber.json`, the UI successfully parses the default config without throwing.\n**Where**: `/Users/tim/.config/openchamber/openchamber.json` and `/Users/tim/dev/ai/mastra-101-new/.openchamber/openchamber.json`\n**Learned**: The minified frontend of `@openchamber/web` lacks `try/catch` around the `/api/fs/read` call for `openchamber.json`. Since the source code isn't checked out locally, creating the config files acts as a permanent environmental fix.","scope":"project","title":"Fixed OpenChamber Chat Error on missing config"}}]}}
